<HEADLINE>
<P>
FALAFEL FAVES; 
</P>
<P>
WHEN ONLY DEEP-FRIED GARBANZO BEANS WILL DO. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amer's Falafel, 17334 Ventura Blvd., Encino. (818) 995-6332. Style: Falafel in 
a shopping center. Setting: Red and white with lots of greenery. 
</P>
<P>
Recommended dishes: Falafel sandwich, $2.10; falafel plate $4.75. 
</P>
<P>
Eat A Pita, 465 N. Fairfax, Los Angeles. (213) 651-0188. Style: For a falafel 
fix on a Saturday. Setting: Pretty in pink. Recommended dishes: Falafel 
sandwich with hummus, $2.95; Falafel plate, $4. 
</P>
<P>
Falafel King, 10940 Weyburn, Westwood. (213) 208-5782. Style: Where frats feed 
on falafel and fritters. Setting: Tacky red shiny booths and open kitchen. 
Recommended dishes: Falafel sandwich, $2.50; fritters, $1. 
</P>
<P>
Tempo, 16610 Ventura Blvd., Encino. (818) 905-5855. Style Dinner house/piano 
bar for the Valley Israeli community. Setting: Bright and open with lovely 
patio. Recommended: Falafel sandwich, $3.50; falafel plate, $6. 
</P>
<P>
Vegetarian Gourmet, 231 N. Beverly Drive, Beverly Hills. (213) 276-1400. Style: 
Falafel served in whole-wheat pita -- ideal for hyper-health fanatics. Setting: 
Indoor garden look. Recommended dishes: Falafel sandwich, $5; falafel plate, 
$5. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
