<HEADLINE>
<P>
BELIZE NOTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read with interest the article on Belize by Bill Belleville in your June 24 
Travel Section ("The Other Caribbean"). In March of this year, three couples, 
including ourselves, rented a home on North Ambergris Caye. 
</P>
<P>
For those who are considering spending some time on the Caye, I would like to 
point out two important facts. 
</P>
<P>
The Caye is divided by El Rio. South Ambergris, where the town of San Pedro is 
located, has the shops, more hotels, restaurants and dive shops. North 
Ambergris has fewer hotels, is more tranquil and water transportation to town 
is provided. 
</P>
<P>
The diving, snorkeling and fishing are indeed excellent. However, the swimming 
is poor due to turtle grass and soft sand. Beautiful-looking beaches, but poor 
for swimming. 
</P>
<P>
Condos and houses are available on both sides of El Rio. Reservations should be 
made as far ahead as possible for the best choices. Our three-bedroom, two-bath 
home, with private dock and daily maid service, plus transportation to San 
Pedro, was $200 U.S. per night. It was very well-equipped. Sundial Travel, 9430 
Warner Ave., Fountain Valley, (714) 962-1176, handled our arrangements. For 
information on houses and condos on the Caye, contact Mary Hawthorne (call 
011-501-2531). She and her partner, Carlos, manage several of the nicer rentals 
on the Caye, and were a great source of information and one of the prime 
reasons our trip was so rewarding. 
</P>
<P>
SARAH U. McBRIDE 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield 
</P>
</TEXT>
