<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMENTS ON CUBA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Horn's cover story on tourism in Cuba ("The Other Caribbean," June 24) was 
remarkably fair and free of cold-war mentality. 
</P>
<P>
Cuba's pristine beaches and paucity of Coca-Cola signs, and the like, sound 
inviting. 
</P>
<P>
Alas, though Cuba welcomes tourists from the United States, our government 
prohibits ordinary tourists from visiting there. I thought it was Communist 
countries that restricted the travel of their citizens to capitalist countries 
to prevent them from learning what capitalism is really like. It seems we need 
our own glasnost here in the U.S.A. 
</P>
<P>
CLIFFORD OLIN 
</P>
<P>
Alhambra 
</P>
