<P>
MAN GETS 3 YEARS FOR BANK ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 31-year-old transient has been sentenced to three years and four months in 
prison for robbing an Oxnard bank, according to FBI officials. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Karl Alexanderson was convicted on federal bank robbery charges after 
pleading guilty before U.S. District Judge William Matthew Byrne in Los Angeles 
on May 21. He also was sentenced to three years probation. 
</P>
