<P>
HIGH-SPEED TRAIN FROM O.C. TO VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to recent news articles, plans are in progress to build a privately 
funded super-train between Las Vegas and Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
It appears that the major reason for this $5-billion expenditure is to more 
easily transport California dollars to Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
Why not use this money to build a casino complex of our own here in California 
and keep all those gambling dollars at home? Think of the revenue available for 
the government from such an operation! 
</P>
<P>
We already have poker and the state lottery, so why not go all the way? We 
could probably outdo Atlantic City, Reno and Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
A super-train sounds nice, but if it's such a good investment, how come the 
proponents are already talking about a subsidy? 
</P>
<P>
Apparently they not only want to transport California dollars to Nevada, they 
want the taxpayers to help pay for it! 
</P>
<P>
AUDIE ASHCRAFT 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 
</P>
</TEXT>
