<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : COUNTYWIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pedestrian, possibly an undocumented immigrant, was run down by at least one 
hit-and-run vehicle and killed late Friday along Interstate 5 near the 
U.S.-Mexico border in San Diego, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
He was struck in a zone where dozens of undocumented pedestrians have been 
killed in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
A network of high-speed roadways forms a barrier for those who have made 
unauthorized crossings into San Diego from Tijuana. 
</P>
<P>
State authorities have placed flashing signs in the area, warning motorists of 
people crossing the road unexpectedly, but the fatalities continue to mount. 
</P>
<P>
The latest victim was identified only as Jose Toribo Barrales. His age and 
address were unknown. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred shortly before 10 p.m., at a spot along I-5 just north of 
the California 905 intersection. 
</P>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol was investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
