<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA GODBEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No plastic pails and rusty trowels here, please. Rising well above the high 
tide line at Will Rogers State Beach on Saturday will be sandcastles and sand 
sculptures worthy of a Main Street gallery. 
</P>
<P>
This, the 9th Annual Sandcastle Competition, is being held to benefit the 
William Z. Landworth Memorial Scholarship Fund. The competition is divided into 
three categories: sandcastle building, sand sculpture and "anything goes," the 
latter for children under 10 years. It will be staged from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
where Pacific Coast Highway and Temescal Canyon Road meet on the beach. The 
public is invited to participate as well as view the sculptures. Entry fee is 
$15. Phone: (213) 380-4595. 
</P>
<P>
It's Sunday morning and you don't have any plans for the afternoon. Dig out a 
pair of walking shoes for an adventure through the streets of West Hollywood. 
Fantastica '90 is a self-guided stroll through West Hollywood's art galleries 
and designer showrooms from noon to 5 p.m. Dancers, poets and clowns will 
provide entertainment, and goodies from top Los Angeles restaurants will be 
served along the way. The afternoon activities will culminate with a juried 
silent auction. Tickets are $25 per person and can be purchased at the plaza of 
the Pacific Design Center, at 8687 Melrose Ave. Phone: (213) 653-0440 for 
information. Proceeds benefit the Los Angeles Free Clinic. CHRISTINA GODBEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
