<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAYS 'DELIGHTED' BY SHERIFF'S POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We were delighted to see the article by John Mitchell (Times, July 19) about 
the improvement of the West Hollywood Sheriff's Station's relationship with the 
lesbian and gay community under Capt. Rachel Burgess. We also applaud Capt. 
Burgess' efforts to meet with lesbian and gay representatives, to sensitize the 
deputies under her command, and to recruit openly lesbian and gay people into 
the force. 
</P>
<P>
As Capt. Burgess noted, while there are lesbians and gay men on the force, none 
of them are currently open about their orientation. We are hopeful that in the 
supportive environment she is fostering they will feel more comfortable about 
being more visible as lesbians and gay men. 
</P>
<P>
JEHAN AGRAMA 
</P>
<P>
Co-president 
</P>
<P>
Gay and Lesbian Alliance 
</P>
<P>
Against Defamation 
</P>
</TEXT>
