shoes that advanced climbers wear. The soles are made of special rubber that 
gives good adhesion, and the fit is snug so the foot is less likely to slip off 
rock nubbins. Flat vertical climbing such as on this man-made wall requires 
more precision in movement than might be needed on a rock slope, said Garrison, 
a Long Beach resident and graduate student at the university who has been 
climbing for more than three years. "It's you against the wall," Garrison said. 
"When you can't make a foothold and fall off, it increases the challenge." MARC 
