<HEADLINE>
<P>
EVELYN HOOKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article on Evelyn Hooker and her pioneering work on homosexual behavior was 
informative and wonderfully free of homophobic journalism. Hooker has 
contributed to the continuing acceptance of gay people in society, and so have 
you by publishing this article and similar reports. 
</P>
<P>
MARIA MEJIA 
</P>
<P>
Gardena 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072990-0154 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 254182 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 29, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Magazine; Page 4B; Magazine Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
102 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGHTING WORDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Children of non-English-speaking parents: The greatest favor you can do for 
your parents is to teach them English -- one word a day. 
</P>
<P>
Without it they are limited in opportunity, isolated in anunreal, small world, 
and they will suffer much prejudice and discrimination. I know, I indulged my 
parents, spoke only Spanish at home (they said they were too busy earning a 
living to learn English). They gave me all they could -- including a college 
education. But when I wanted to take a job in New York, I couldn't go. My 
parents couldn't buy food without me to speak English. 
</P>
<P>
RAMONA ALVAREZ 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
