<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOMADS BEATEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Salt Lake Sting shut out the San Diego Nomads, 2-0, in a Western Soccer 
League game Saturday in Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
Craig Huft scored the Sting's first goal 43 minutes into the game. George 
Pastor followed up with a second goal before halftime on a penalty kick as the 
Sting improved to 12-7. 
</P>
<P>
The Nomads (7-10) will return to Southwestern College to play the California 
Emperors Aug. 4. 
</P>
