<TEXT>
<P>
Forward Johnny Newman joined the Charlotte Hornets when the New York Knicks 
decided not to match an offer sheet for the restricted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
The Knicks had 15 days to match the offer for the 6-foot-7, 190-pound Newman, 
who averaged 12.9 points last season. They get no compensation for his loss. 
</P>
<P>
The deal reportedly was worth $5 million for four years. 
</P>
