<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former USC offensive lineman Jeff Bregel, who came to the San Francisco 49ers' 
camp early and was expected to contend for a starting job at right guard this 
year, announced his retirement. 
</P>
<P>
Bregel also walked out of summer camp last August, saying that his back was 
injured and that he wanted to retire. 
</P>
<P>
He returned to camp and started the first three games of the season before he 
was replaced by Guy McIntyre in the fourth game. 
</P>
<P>
Bregel reacted by skipping practice and was suspended without pay Sept. 29. He 
was placed on injured reserve Oct. 4 because of his back and underwent disk 
surgery Nov. 28, finishing the season on injured reserve. 
</P>
<P>
Bregel, a second-round draft pick in 1987, recently signed a contract and was 
scheduled to make $200,000 this season. 
