<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH SURELOCK; 
</P>
<P>
THE SILICON SLEUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dancinginthepark joined SURELOCK's growing list of turf front-runners who have 
faded at Del Mar, but at least she managed to finish second ($7.20) for a $64 
profit in the fifth race. However, all but $4 of that profit evaporated in the 
eighth when two of its exacta picks, Stylish Star and Nikishka, ran 2-3 behind 
$47.20 longshot Jabalina Brown. 
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK's bets for today are $40 to win on Exclusive Partner in the seventh 
race and a $20 late double of Sunny Blossom in the eighth race to Horsche in 
the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK's Sat. Bankroll $1,740 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's Profit $4 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $1,744 
</P>
<P>
Janice Goldinger's $5 exacta box paid a handsome $82.20 on $2 in the fifth 
race. She lost her flat bets on Belle Poitrine in the fifth and D'Or Ruckus in 
the sixth, but still cleared $146.25 for the day. 
</P>
<P>
Janice will bet $100 to win and place on My Prayer in the ninth race today. 
</P>
<P>
Janice's Sat. Bankroll $1,900 
</P>
<P>
