Profit (in this instance) as any schoolchild could tell Campbell, is the sales 
price less the selling expenses and the cost price (including any costs of 
improvement). Period. 
</P>
<P>
Shame on the L.A. Times for publishing this simple writer's theory as if touted 
by an expert. 
</P>
<P>
CLIVE KENNEDY 
