<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
<P>
* For late-summer show of color -- plant petunias, marigolds, zinnias and 
lobelia. 
</P>
<P>
* Check the lawn and garden for pest and diseases. Apply the proper controls 
immediately. 
</P>
<P>
* It's a good idea to take down your hanging baskets every now and then and 
give them a thorough soaking by either dunking them in a bucket or by running 
the water from a hose very slowly over a period of time. 
</P>
<P>
* Faded annuals can be quickly replaced with fresh new plants from your 
nursery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; List 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072990-0199 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 254293 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 29, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
