<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS: CONDOS IN L.A.'S RANCHO PARK AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beverly Green Plaza, featuring 12 two-bedroom condominiums in a three-story 
building, opens today in the Rancho Park district of Los Angeles, near Century 
City and the Hillcrest Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
The one-level units are offered in four plans, all averaging about 1,800 square 
feet, priced from $430,000-$490,000, according to a spokesman for the builder, 
Hoang Tai Development Corp. 
</P>
<P>
Features include nine-foot-high ceilings, fireplaces, two private balconies, a 
den with a wet bar and and kitchens with a breakfast nook or breakfast bar. The 
monthly association dues are $240 and move-ins are scheduled to begin in late 
August and early September. 
</P>
<P>
A sales office and one furnished model staffed by Pamela Pang of RE/PROS 
Brokerage Inc. is open daily, except Tuesdays and Fridays from 1 to 4 p.m. at 
9880 Vidor Drive, a block north of Pico Boulevard at Roxbury Drive. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Anaheim Hills Homes 
</P>
<P>
Summit Pointe at The Summit of Anaheim Hills opens today in Anaheim Hills, with 
200 large single-family houses planned in the gated community. 
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the development by the Irvine-based Baldwin Co. has 23 
four-, five- and six-bedroom houses with in four two-story plans with 3,541 to 
4,857 square feet of living area. 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled for February move-ins, houses in the initial increment are on lots up 
to 3/4 of an acre and are priced from $589,000 to $695,000. Features include 
four-car garages, interior laundry rooms, upstairs media centers, libraries and 
maid's quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Homeowner association dues of about $170 a month cover upkeep of slopes, common 
areas and a 12-acre private park. Four furnished models are open 10 a.m. to 6 
p.m. daily at Taylor Court at Serrano Avenue, reached from the southbound Weir 
Canyon Road exit of the Riverside (91) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Lancaster Development 
</P>
<P>
El Encanto, a 42-unit single-family development of four- and five-bedroom 
houses, opens today in Lancaster. 
</P>
<P>
The 10 houses in the first phase are offered in three two-story floor plans 
with 2,036 to 2,338 square feet, with nine elevations. They are priced from 
$164,900 to $184,000. 
</P>
<P>
The developer is Harwood Homes/J.P. Eliopulos Enterprises Inc. Move-ins are 
planned for October. 
</P>
<P>
Features include attached three-car garages with roll-up metal doors, concrete 
tile roofs, Bose Acoustimass audio systems, vaulted ceilings, raised-panel 
interior doors and hardwood or ceramic-tiled entries. 
</P>
<P>
Three models are open daily, except Wednesday and Thursday, from 10 a.m. to 6 
p.m. at Avenue K and 12th Street East, reached from the eastbound Avenue K exit 
of the Antelope Valley (14) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Carlsbad Project 
</P>
<P>
Mediterranean architecture is featured in Hillgate, a 32-home project by 
Torrance-based Wesco Development Corp. opening today in Carlsbad about 1 1/2 
miles from the Pacific Ocean. 
</P>
<P>
Nine three-, four- and five-bedroom single-family houses are offered in five 
plans with 2,267 to 2,914 square feet, priced from $349,900 to $429,900. 
September move-ins are planned. 
</P>
<P>
Offered in nine elevations, the houses feature private courtyards, up to three 
bathrooms, fireplaces, skylights, volume ceilings and skylights. On-site 
recreational facilities include a pool, a spa and an outdoor picnic area. The 
monthly association fee is $190. 
</P>
<P>
The sales office is open daily from 10:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. at 2908 Wintergreen 
Drive, reached from the eastbound California 78 exit of the San Diego (5) 
Freeway to the southbound El Camino Real exit. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Homes in Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
Calabria Villas, a gated enclave of 12 three-bedroom single-family detached 
houses on small lots, opens today in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
The three-bedroom houses by Laguna Hills-based Briggs Development Corp. are 
offered in two two-story plans with 1,743 to 1,795 square feet, priced from 
$299,900 to $349,000. 
</P>
<P>
Features include Mediterranean exteriors, two-car garages with direct access; 
vaulted ceilings in most rooms and wood-burning fireplaces. The monthly 
association fee is about $49 and August move-ins are planned. 
</P>
<P>
The sales office is open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at 2524 Orange Ave., near 
the intersection of Del Mar Avenue, reached from the Newport Boulevard exit of 
the Costa Mesa (55) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Links-Oriented Homes 
</P>
<P>
Mirada on the Green, a golf-course-oriented single-family development with 150 
houses, opens today in Moreno Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The 16 three- four- and five-bedroom houses in the initial phase range in size 
from 2,653 to 3,250 square feet and are priced from $244,000 to $344,000. They 
have two to three baths. 
</P>
<P>
The builder is Barratt American Inc. and first phase move-ins are expected in 
November. Mirada on the Green is in the Moreno Valley Ranch planned community, 
which has a public golf course. Mirada has no association fee. 
</P>
<P>
Four furnished models are open daily from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. at 15635 Oliver 
St., reached from the Moreno Beach Drive exit of the Pomona (60) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Gated Development 
</P>
<P>
Cape West, a gated development of 132 single-family houses by JHJ Holdings 
Inc., opens today in Sepulveda. 
</P>
<P>
The first phase of 30 three- and four-bedroom houses ranges in price from 
$245,950 to $250,950. The development's name comes from its Cape Cod-style 
architecture. 
</P>
<P>
The houses are offered in three floor plans ranging in size from 1,840 to 1,900 
square feet, with two-car garages, wood-burning fireplaces, ceramic tile 
entries, indoor laundry rooms, storage areas and master bedroom suites. 
Immediate move-ins are available. 
</P>
<P>
A monthly association fee of $82.96 pays for the common area maintenance of the 
project, located on a private street accessed by a telephone entry gate. The 
sales office is open from noon to 5 p.m. daily except Wednesdays and Thursdays 
at 9155 Noble Ave., east of Sepulveda Boulevard between Nordhoff and Devonshire 
streets, reached from the eastbound Devonshire exit of the San Diego (405) 
Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Oceanfront Condos 
</P>
<P>
Pier Colony, a development of 130 oceanfront condominiums by California 
Resorts/Haseko Associates, opens today in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five of the loft, one- and two-bedroom units have been sold. The units 
range in size from 861 to 1,492 square feet and are priced from $190,000 to 
$610,000. October move-ins are scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
The monthly association fee ranges from $240 to $280 and covers upkeep of a 
pool, spa, clubhouse and secured parking. 
</P>
<P>
Four furnished models are open from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. daily at 200 Pacific 
Coast Highway, reached from the southbound Beach Boulevard exit of the San 
Diego (405) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Palmdale Project 
</P>
<P>
One- and two-story plans are featured in Allegro, a 94-unit single-family 
development by Harwood Homes/Marshall Wengrow Inc. opening today in Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
The 21 four- and five-bedroom houses are available in three plans, ranging from 
1,832 to 2,362 square feet, and nine exterior treatments. Move-ins are planned 
for October. 
</P>
<P>
All plans have the option of converting one of the extra bedrooms into a master 
suite retreat. Other conversions are possible with bedrooms becoming dens, 
libraries, media rooms or offices. Standard features include Bose Acoustimass 
sound systems, tile roofs and three-car garages with segmented metal doors. 
</P>
<P>
Three models are open daily, except Wednesday and Thursday, from 10 a.m. to 6 
p.m. at Avenue R-8 and 57th Street East, reached from the eastbound Avenue S 
exit of the Antelope Valley (14) Freeway to 47th Street East and north on that 
street to R-8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
