<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRIME-TIME FLICKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Wilmington 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Explorers (KCOP Friday at 8 p.m.), a 1985 kids-in-space adventure with the 
euphonious team of Ethan Hawke and River Phoenix, has some of the antic wit and 
frenzied visual imagination director Joe Dante pumped into the Gremlins movies 
but, at the end, it turns into a crazy sundae with the nuts on top: a space 
cartoon climax full of nyark-nyark goofiness. 
</P>
